race.comment: ALTERNATE (3) is yet to win at the mile but has good form for this. Turned in a strong run two back at Caulfield Heath then started favourite at Wangaratta but blew the start and was up against it from then on. Stretches out a little in journey but drawn the inside and for a soft run and looks hard to beat. BELLMAN (1) was a few lengths away in the Bong Bong Cup two back then raced over further last time and was safely held. Freshened for this, the mile suits and aided by the claim. Can improve sharply. TOP ARCTIC (6) returned from a spell at Yarra Valley and ran on hard for a close-up fourth. Strips fitter and the extra ground suits. Leading player. TRINITY'S D'ORO (9) doesn't win out of turn but has put together a string of good runs. Drawn well and rates a top chance on best. UNQUESTIONABLY (4) resumed in the same race as TRINITY'S D'ORO and finished alongside him in fifth. Fitter and has a good second-up record.
